title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.3: SOCIAL PROTECTION ENABLING ENVIRONMENT

description.narrative: Output 4.3: National Government and counties have increased capacity to formulate and implement child-centred social protection policies, legal and coordination frameworks, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 4 - Social inclusion: An increased number of children from the poorest & most vulnerable households benefit from shock- responsive & integrated social protection interventions, as well as from child-specific policies

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the finalization of the revised Policy and Investment Plan for social protection in Kenya, expected to be submitted and approved by Cabinet early 2022. UNICEF led in convening and outreach efforts towards the establishment and operationalization of the SGSP, of which it continues to co-chair with FCDO involving a multisectoral collaboration with other development partners as well as focal points in GoK. On social protection inclusion and universality UNICEF spearheaded theUniversal Child Benefit;(UCB) programme discussions as well as the support towards the STRIDE programme on disability to advance the investment plan pillars. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/12/2021
